data.description: Nestled amidst the serene Santa Cruz Mountains, it unveils a private oasis awaiting the realization of your dreams. This meticulously prepared 1.796-acre lot meticulously groomed stands ready for the construction of your Playon modular home 20X60, the owner has spent over 70K getting it ready they have all the permits and the plans. Or you can build a single family. Step into this forested haven, where ancient Big Basin Redwood trees, affectionately dubbed 'The Giants,' have undergone a majestic rebirth. Ascend to the plateau atop the hill-knoll, where breathtaking sunsets paint the horizon, casting a golden hue over the expansive green expanse that stretches before you. Immerse yourself in the rich history of this locale, nestled within the protected confines of Little Basin Park, once the exclusive domain of the Hewlett Packard Company. Step into your future and behold the endless possibilities that await within this sanctuary of nature's bounty.
